## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose
This document outlines the functional and non-functional requirements for Amane, a web-based platform designed to support survivors of violence, abuse, and bullying in Ethiopia. Amane provides integrated tools for anonymous reporting, counseling, community engagement, legal aid tracking, and career support — all within a culturally sensitive, trauma-informed, and privacy-first environment.

This SRS serves as a foundation for design, development, testing, and stakeholder alignment.

### 1.2 Scope
Amane is a Progressive Web Application (PWA) accessible via desktop and mobile browsers. It targets:
- Survivors of gender-based violence (GBV), domestic abuse, bullying, and harassment
- Children, women, and men across urban and rural Ethiopia
- Caregivers, legal advocates, mental health professionals, and NGOs

Included Features:
- Anonymous incident reporting with smart triage
- Case tracking dashboard (“My Journey”)
- Secure counseling & mentorship matching
- Verified resource directory with interactive map
- Community forums (“Safe Circles”)
- Storytelling hub (text/audio/illustration)
- Event calendar for healing workshops
- Job portal for ethical employment
- Wellness tools (breathing, affirmations)
- Multilingual support (Amharic, Oromo, Tigrinya, English)

Excluded:
- Mobile app (native iOS/Android) — though PWA works on phones
- Real-time emergency dispatch (e.g., automatic police alert)
- Financial transactions or payment processing

