## 3. Functional Requirements

### 3.1 User Management (Optional)
| ID | Requirement | Priority |
|----|------------|----------|
| FR-01 | The system shall allow users to use the platform without creating an account. | High |
| FR-02 | The system shall allow optional account creation for caregivers or advocates. | Medium |
| FR-03 | The system shall support login via email or phone (if account created). | Medium |

### 3.2 Incident Reporting
| ID | Requirement | Priority |
|----|------------|----------|
| FR-04 | The system shall provide a smart reporting form that guides users through context-aware questions (type of abuse, perpetrator, location). | High |
| FR-05 | The system shall allow anonymous submission with zero IP or device logging. | Critical |
| FR-06 | The system shall support uploading text, images, or audio (max 10MB). | Medium |
| FR-07 | The system shall auto-translate the form into the user’s selected language. | High |
| FR-08 | The system shall allow saving a draft locally (browser storage). | Medium |

### 3.3 Case Tracking & Dashboard
| ID | Requirement | Priority |
|----|------------|----------|
| FR-09 | The system shall generate a unique, anonymous Case ID upon submission. | High |
| FR-10 | The system shall display a visual “My Journey” timeline showing report status, counselor assignment, and next steps. | High |
| FR-11 | The system shall allow exporting the case timeline as a PDF. | Medium |

### 3.4 Counseling & Support
| ID | Requirement | Priority |
|----|------------|----------|
| FR-12 | The system shall match users with available counselors based on language, gender preference, and expertise. | High |
| FR-13 | The system shall provide secure text and video chat (via embedded Jitsi). | High |
| FR-14 | The system shall auto-delete chat logs after 7 days unless user opts to save. | Critical |

### 3.5 Resource Directory & Map
| ID | Requirement | Priority |
|----|------------|----------|
| FR-15 | The system shall display a filterable map of verified resources (shelters, legal aid, hospitals). | High |
| FR-16 | The system shall show transport instructions (e.g., “Take blue minibus from Meskel Square”). | Medium |
| FR-17 | The system shall allow NGOs to submit and verify new resources via admin panel. | Medium |

### 3.6 Community & Storytelling
| ID | Requirement | Priority |
|----|------------|----------|
| FR-18 | The system shall allow users to submit stories via text, voice, or drawing. | Medium |
| FR-19 | The system shall host private forums (“Safe Circles”) moderated by trained volunteers. | High |
| FR-20 | The system shall allow emoji-only reactions (no open comments) to reduce conflict. | Medium |

### 3.7 Events & Jobs
| ID | Requirement | Priority |
|----|------------|----------|
| FR-21 | The system shall allow NGOs to post healing events (in-person/virtual) with RSVP. | Medium |
| FR-22 | The system shall host a job portal for ethical employers in social sectors. | Medium |
| FR-23 | The system shall require job posters to agree to a code of ethics (trauma-informed, non-discriminatory). | Medium |

### 3.8 Safety & Privacy
| ID | Requirement | Priority |
|----|------------|----------|
| FR-24 | The system shall include a “Panic Mode” button that clears session data and redirects to a fake page (e.g., government website). | Critical |
| FR-25 | The system shall work offline for core features (emergency contacts, breathing exercises). | High |
| FR-26 | The system shall not store user data unless explicitly consented. | Critical |

